cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DL 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the annotation of temporal information over discourse, which is a natural language processing task. It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as temporal reasoning is an important aspect of AI. Additionally, the creation of tools for validating and repairing TimeML resources may fall under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the mention of ISO-TimeML suggests that this paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.DL (Digital Libraries).
